Which [Q] represents the 4-MeI concentration and I0 and I are the intrinsic fluorescence intensity without 4-MeI and in the presence of 4-MeI, respectively while C is constant [2]. The Stern-Volmer constant (Ksv) is the calibration curve slope in which resulted 0.1871 mL ng−1. To verify the validity of the proposed method, several analytical parameters such as limits of detection (LOD, S/N = 3), limits of quantification (LOQ, S/N = 10), linear dynamic range (LDR), coefficient of determination (R2), relative standard deviation (RSD) for intra-day and inter-day under optimum condition were achieved (Table 1
                        ). The fluorescence emission spectra and Stern-Volmer plot resulted from the developed sensor in the presence of different concentrations of 4-MeI are shown in Fig. 8
                        . By considering the standard deviations of upper and lower concentration ranges and calculating F-test, the Fexperiment < Fcritical is obtained and the unweighted calibration plot (Fig. 8) is depicted.

To investigate the applicability of the proposed method, eight caffeine-free sodas (black sodas), four brands A, B, C and D, were analyzed and 4-MeI was conveniently detected under the optimum condition. These samples were fortified with 4-MeI at 5, 50 and 100 ng mL−1 levels and analyzed using the BioTek microplate reader under the optimum condition. Relative recoveries (RR%) were calculated and results are shown in Table 2
                        . The analytical parameters of the current method are compared with other relevant techniques (Table 3
                        ). The results in this study are well comparable to other methods used for the detection of 4-MeI.
